   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 56, 27.927419}", 
    "history" -> {"12", "13.1", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"mixed state", "density operator"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "PartialTrace[mat, {i, j, ...}] takes the partial trace of the matrix mat \
over the ith, jth, ... qubits and returns the resulting reduced matrix. \
PartialTrace[mat, {d1, d2, ...}, {i, j, ...}] assumes species of dimensions \
d1, d2, .... and takes the partial trace over the ith, jth, ... species. \
PartialTrace[vec, {i, j, ...}] or PartialTrace[vec, {d1, d2, ...}, {i, j, \
...}] is the same but operate on the dyadic product of vector vec with \
itself. The result is a square matrix, i.e., the reduced density matrix, not \
a pure-state column vector any longer. PartialTrace[expr, {a1, a2, ...}, {s1, \
s2, ...}] returns the partial trace of quantum state expr over the subsystems \
s1, s2, ... in the total system consisting of a1, a2, .... PartialTrace[expr, \
{s1, s2, ...}] finds the total system from expr and {s1, s2, ...}.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "PartialTrace", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "PartialTrace", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/PartialTrace"}},
